        "id": 1078923
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-02-29T21:59:00Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "SInce you  are not using the depth texture, you should use a render buffer instead.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 409,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 409,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "636d9aac8a01f7a5783dea03a4fece7758b3a687",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "02feade5_f00da817",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/gl-widget.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 409,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-01T00:12:15Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "My initial version used a renderbuffer, however the program would hang on the call to mGLES2-\u003eglGenRenderbuffersEXT. I wasn\u0027t too keen on debugging it, so decided to go with a texture attachment. What is the disadvantage of using a texture for the dept attachment vs a renderbuffer?",
      "parentUuid": "c26bb568_b437ad96",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 409,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 409,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "636d9aac8a01f7a5783dea03a4fece7758b3a687",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e211990a_5649f205",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/gl-widget.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 409,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078923
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-02T00:04:30Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Renderbuffers are not queriable, while textures are. The GL can therefore store the data in a more efficient manner. This is especially true for depth buffers. I would highly recommend you use a render buffer. You shouldn\u0027t need to use any extension for it.",
      "parentUuid": "02feade5_f00da817",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 409,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 409,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "636d9aac8a01f7a5783dea03a4fece7758b3a687",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e27a7932_50c4335d",
        "filename": "android/skin/qt/gl-widget.cpp",
        "patchSetId": 2
      },
      "lineNbr": 409,
      "author": {
        "id": 1078773
      },
      "writtenOn": "2016-03-02T06:21:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "As it turned out, we have a bug in emugl that caused this strange behavior. After fixing it, I am able to use renderbuffer objects. I will send out the fix as a separate change.",
      "parentUuid": "e211990a_5649f205",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 409,
        "startChar": 16,
        "endLine": 409,
        "endChar": 23
      },
      "revId": "636d9aac8a01f7a5783dea03a4fece7758b3a687",
      "serverId": "85c56323-6fa9-3386-8a01-6480fb634889",
      "unresolved": false
    },
